
[1]openly

   OPENLY, adv. o'pnly.

   1. Publicly; not in private; without secrecy; as, to avow our sins and
   follies openly.

   How grossly and openly do many of us contradict the precepts of the
   gospel by our ungodliness and worldly lusts!

   2. Plainly; evidently; without reserve or disguise.
